<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-901-146  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 901 146.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Nov 20 1989 n342 p43(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>U.S., British still planning for OS/2.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hubbard, Holly.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A survey in Great Britain and the US made by Romtec plc finds thatusers are preparing for a strong market emergence of the OS/2operating system.andP;  The poll of England's top companies finds that33.6 percent are planning their MIS strategies around OS/2.andO;Almost half of those polled plan to have their microcomputersrunning OS/2 by the end of 1991.andP;  Two percent of respondents among250 UK corporate sites questioned plan to be running OS/2 by theend of 1989; the number is expected to rise to 11 percent by 1991.andO;However, the survey also reveals little belief among users thatOS/2 will seriously infiltrate the market until mid-1990 or 1991.andO;Few existing plans were found among respondents for purchasingOS/2; a lack of available applications appears to be the primefactor in this trend, while a belief that existing OS/2applications do not make full use of OS/2 is a contributingfactor.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Romtec PLC (surveys).andO;Topic:     OS-2EnglandMISMarket PenetrationUser SurveyPurchasesMarket SharePlanning.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   OS/2 in the U.K. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>